---
import DocsLayout from '../layouts/DocsLayout.astro';
import CodeWindow from '../components/CodeWindow.astro';

const title = "Quickstart — RCAN Protocol";
const description = "From zero to your first RCAN message in 5 minutes.";
---

<DocsLayout title={title} description={description}>

  <h1>Quickstart</h1>
  <p class="lead text-xl text-text-muted mb-10">From zero to your first RCAN message in 5 minutes.</p>

  <!-- Step 1 -->
  <h2 id="install">
    <span class="text-accent font-mono text-lg mr-2">01</span>Install the SDK
  </h2>

  <CodeWindow language="bash" title="Terminal" code={`pip install rcan

# Optional extras
pip install rcan[http]    # registry client (httpx)
pip install rcan[crypto]  # Ed25519 message signing
pip install rcan[all]     # everything

# TypeScript / JavaScript
npm install rcan-ts`} />

  <!-- Step 2 -->
  <h2 id="robot-uri">
    <span class="text-accent font-mono text-lg mr-2">02</span>Build a Robot URI
  </h2>
  <p>Every robot has a globally unique, resolvable address. No more "which unit was it?"</p>

  <CodeWindow language="python" title="address.py" code={`from rcan import RobotURI

uri = RobotURI.build(
    manufacturer="acme",
    model="robotarm",
    version="v2",
    device_id="unit-001",
)
print(uri)
# rcan://registry.rcan.dev/acme/robotarm/v2/unit-001

# Parse from a string
uri = RobotURI.parse("rcan://registry.rcan.dev/acme/robotarm/v2/unit-001")
print(uri.namespace)      # acme/robotarm
print(uri.registry_url)   # https://registry.rcan.dev/registry/...`} />

  <!-- Step 3 -->
  <h2 id="confidence-gate">
    <span class="text-accent font-mono text-lg mr-2">03</span>Gate on AI Confidence
  </h2>
  <p>The gate doesn't trust the model — that's the point. The model is right 99.99% of the time. The gate catches the 0.01%.</p>

  <CodeWindow language="python" title="gate.py" code={`from rcan import RCANMessage, ConfidenceGate

gate = ConfidenceGate(threshold=0.8)
confidence = 0.91  # from your AI model

if gate.allows(confidence):
    msg = RCANMessage(
        cmd="move_forward",
        target=uri,
        params={"distance_m": 1.0},
        confidence=confidence,
        model_identity="Qwen2.5-7B-Q4",
    )
    print(msg.to_json(indent=2))
else:
    print(f"Blocked: confidence {confidence} < threshold {gate.threshold}")`} />

  <p>For high-stakes actions, add a <code>HiTLGate</code> to require explicit human approval. See <a href="/spec/#section-16">§16 AI Accountability</a>.</p>

  <!-- Step 4 -->
  <h2 id="audit-chain">
    <span class="text-accent font-mono text-lg mr-2">04</span>Create a Tamper-Evident Audit Record
  </h2>
  <p>Every safety-critical action can be sealed into an HMAC-chained record — forensic-grade proof of what the system did, when, at what confidence.</p>

  <CodeWindow language="python" title="audit.py" code={`from rcan import CommitmentRecord
from rcan.audit import AuditChain

chain = AuditChain(secret="your-hmac-secret")

record = chain.append(CommitmentRecord(
    action="move_forward",
    robot_uri=str(uri),
    confidence=0.91,
    model_identity="Qwen2.5-7B-Q4",
    params={"distance_m": 1.0},
    safety_approved=True,
))

print(f"Sealed: {record.content_hash[:12]}...")
print(f"Chain valid: {chain.verify_all()}")  # True

# Export JSONL for long-term storage or audit
with open("audit.jsonl", "w") as f:
    f.write(chain.to_jsonl())`} />

  <!-- Step 5 -->
  <h2 id="register">
    <span class="text-accent font-mono text-lg mr-2">05</span>Register Your Robot
  </h2>
  <p>Get a globally unique RRN (Robot Registry Number). Free.</p>

  <CodeWindow language="bash" title="Terminal" code={`# If using OpenCastor — built into the setup wizard
castor wizard
# → Step 13: Register with rcan.dev? [Y/n]  →  ✅ RRN-00000042

# Or standalone
castor register --config myrobot.rcan.yaml`} />

  <!-- Step 6 -->
  <h2 id="validate">
    <span class="text-accent font-mono text-lg mr-2">06</span>Validate Your Config
  </h2>

  <CodeWindow language="bash" title="Terminal" code={`# Check L1/L2/L3 conformance
rcan-validate config myrobot.rcan.yaml

# Expected output:
# ✅ L1 — Addressing + message format: passed
# ✅ L2 — Auth + confidence gates: passed
# ⚠️  L3 — hitl_gates not configured (§16)
# Result: L2 (1 warning)

# Or with OpenCastor
castor compliance --config myrobot.rcan.yaml`} />

  <!-- What's Next -->
  <h2 id="next">What's next</h2>

  <div class="not-prose grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4 mt-6">
    {[
      { href: '/spec/', label: 'Protocol Spec', desc: 'Full RCAN v1.2 specification' },
      { href: '/conformance/', label: 'Conformance Tests', desc: 'L1/L2/L3 test suite' },
      { href: 'https://github.com/continuonai/rcan-py', label: 'rcan-py on GitHub', desc: 'Python SDK source + issues' },
      { href: 'https://github.com/continuonai/rcan-ts', label: 'rcan-ts on GitHub', desc: 'TypeScript SDK source + issues' },
      { href: 'https://github.com/craigm26/OpenCastor', label: 'OpenCastor', desc: 'Robot runtime with RCAN built in' },
      { href: '/registry/submit/', label: 'Register a Robot', desc: 'Get your free RRN' },
    ].map(({ href, label, desc }) => (
      <a href={href} target={href.startsWith('http') ? '_blank' : undefined} rel={href.startsWith('http') ? 'noopener noreferrer' : undefined}
        class="block p-4 border border-white/8 rounded-xl hover:border-accent/40 hover:bg-accent/5 transition-all duration-200">
        <div class="text-white font-semibold text-sm">{label}</div>
        <div class="text-text-muted text-xs mt-1">{desc}</div>
      </a>
    ))}
  </div>

</DocsLayout>
